Otherwise, it will be visible to all users.

targetOrgs.description: DominoIds of orgs whose users will receive this notification.

targetRoles.description: Ids of Roles. Users that have any of these Roles will receive this notification.

targetUsers.description: DominoIds of users who will receive this notification.

orgs.description: Names and IDs of orgs whose users will receive this notification

roles.description: Names and Ids of Roles. Users that have any of these Roles will receive this notification.

users.description: Names and IDs of users who will receive this notification

ids.description: IDs of notifications to be marked as read

200.description:
Scenarios:
If the log retriever got NO logs, then the client should expect * an empty `logContent` array from the returned LogSet.

If the log retriever was done fetching ALL of the logs, then the client should expect * `isComplete = true` * `paginationFilter.limit = 0` from the returned LogSet.

If the log retriever was NOT done fetching all of the logs, then the client should expect * `isComplete = false` * `paginationFilter` encoding the next `offset` or `latestTimeNano` of the last log line fetched by the retriever. from the returned LogSet.

parameters.description: Max number of log lines to fetch. Will be overridden by the configuration's limit if this value exceeds the configuration's limit, or if this value is not provided.
parameters.name: limit

parameters.description: The index of the current body of logs to start fetching from. 0 by default and typically won't be used for a timestamp-based offset log fetching strategy.
parameters.name: offset

parameters.description: The epoch time in nanoseconds to start fetching from, such as "1543538813745986325". "0" by default and will typically be used for a timestamp-based offset log fetching strategy.
parameters.name: latestTimeNano

200.description:
Scenarios:
If the log retriever got NO logs, then the client should expect * an empty `logContent` array from the returned LogSet.

If the log retriever was done fetching ALL of the logs, then the client should expect * `isComplete = true` * `paginationFilter.limit = 0` from the returned LogSet.

If the log retriever was NOT done fetching all of the logs, then the client should expect * `isComplete = false` * `paginationFilter` encoding the next `offset` or `latestTimeNano` of the last log line fetched by the retriever. from the returned LogSet.
